meanings.definition: To defeat or surpass in a competition or contest.
meanings.sent1: She outduels her opponents in every race.
meanings.sent2: The athlete outduels his competitors with ease.
meanings.sent3: The squirrel outdueling the birds for the last acorn was quite a sight.
meanings.sent4: Her determination to outduel any obstacle in her path is inspiring.
meanings.sent5: The knight outdueling the dragon in the final battle was a heroic moment.

meanings.definition: To outperform or outshine someone in a competitive situation.
meanings.sent1: He always outduels his colleagues in sales.
meanings.sent2: The singer outduels the other contestants with her powerful voice.
meanings.sent3: The clown outdueling the magician in a magic trick was unexpected.
meanings.sent4: Her creativity outduels all others in the art class.
meanings.sent5: The sun outdueling the stars in brightness during the day is a natural phenomenon.
